  "prompt": "What guidelines are in place regarding passport photos in Canada?",
  "response": "In Canada, passport photo guidelines are strict to ensure that all passport photos meet the required specifications. Here are the key guidelines for passport photos in Canada:\n\n1. **Size Requirements**:\n   - The photo must be 50 mm wide by 70 mm high.\n   - The face must take up between 31 mm and 36 mm from chin to crown.\n\n2. **Background**:\n   - The background must be plain white or light-colored without any shadows or objects.\n   - No textures or patterns.\n\n3. **Quality**:\n   - The photo must be in color and of high quality, with no underexposure or overexposure.\n   - The image should be sharp, clear, and without any reflections.\n\n4. **Pose and Expression**:\n   - The subject must have a neutral expression with both eyes open and mouth closed.\n   - The head must be straight and not tilted, with the face visible and centered.\n\n5. **Glasses**:\n   - Glasses are allowed but should not cause glare and should not cover the eyes. The eyes must be clearly visible.\n   - The frame must not cover any part of the eyes.\n\n6. **Head Coverings**:\n   - Head coverings for religious or medical reasons are permitted, but the face must be fully visible from ear to ear and from chin to the top of the forehead.\n\n7. **Children**:\n   - Photos of infants and young children must follow the same guidelines. For infants, an adult may hold them, but the adult's hands must not be visible.\n\n8. **Professional Standards**:\n   - It is often recommended to have passport photos taken by a professional photographer familiar with Canada's passport photo requirements.\n\n9. **Submission**:\n   - Photos should be printed on high-quality photo paper and not altered or digitally manipulated (other than standard retouching for blemishes).\n\nIt is important to check the latest requirements directly from the Government of Canada\u2019s official website or the application guidelines, as specifications can change.",
